title: Thayumanavan
subTitle: A police officer invites three prisoners to his house for Diwali. As they celebrate, the prisoners tell him why they hate women.

title: Azhagarsamy
subTitle: Thayama gets money from a landlord in order to save her husband and promises to give her child in return. Things turn for the worst when the rich man wants to marry off his daughter to Thayama's son.

title: Vedham Pudhithu
subTitle: Vaidehi belongs to an orthodox Brahmin family and falls in love with Sankarapandi who is from a different caste. Their love is disapproved by her father but is accepted by Sankarapandi's family.

title: Makkal Aatchi
subTitle: Sethupathi, a common man, gets lucky when he accidentally finds a large amount of money in a truck. He decides to use the money to enter politics and ends up becoming the chief minister of the state.

title: Singaravelan
subTitle: Velan's mother tells him to find his cousin, Sumathi, who lives in the city and marry her. Velan sets out to find her with the help of a childhood photograph.

title: Ulle Veliye
subTitle: Gajendran, a corrupt police officer, has only one aim in life, making money, but one day gets caught by the anti-corruption authorities. Things change when a woman loses her reputation and her life in order to save him.

title: Vaidhegi Vanthachu
subTitle: A naive Karupan is forced by his lecherous MLA boss to marry a girl who snubbed the politician. The unwilling bride, turning vengeance into redemption, decides to reform her husband.

title: Simmasanam
subTitle: Sakthivel and Thangarasu are stepbrothers who don't get along with each other. Their differences become more apparent as they start finding out their father's killer.
